CLERIC CLERICS

Clerics have an ancient belief in not carrying sharp weapons.  Hence, they can
only wield bludgeoning weapons.  This class gives you the wisdom of peace,
blessing and healing, though it is possible to learn more violent spells.

All clerics in the Dragonlance setting (and hence, on this MUD) are actually
priests and priestesses of a specific god or goddess.  The spells that any
priest may cast is a power that their god has granted them - hence, priests
of different gods and goddesses will have a different spell selection, which
depends mainly on their god's beliefs and standard duties.

NOTE: All dieties grant at least minor access to the spheres of healing and
creation - although this may not be necessarily be true to the diety's beliefs,
we understand that it can exceptionally hard to play a priest character without
these spells, which are generally well-recognized as the cleric's forte.  This
does not mean that all dieties grant major access to these spheres.

See also: PRACTICE, SPELLS
