DRAGONLANCE DL

It is a world of epic heroes, of perilous passages, unimaginable dangers
and unparalleled beauty.  On the continent of Ansalon the traveler will 
meet bold Knights of Solamnia, sworn to defend goodness and right, and
to uphold the Oath and the Measure. The unwary may be confronted by
a company of Knights of Takhisis, pledged to the service of the Dark 
Queen. The forests hold perils and promise at the hands of the elven
nations: the proud Qualinesti and Silvanesti, as well as their 
mysterious cousins the wild Kagonesti. 

Beneath the mountains delve the dwarves--gruff and solitary. And along
the roads and byways wander the kender: perpetually curious, endearingly
childlike--and scrupulously avoided by the inhabitants of Ansalon for 
their tendency to "borrow" things. 

Above all, Dragonlance is a world of dragons. The evil chromatic dragons
are willing servants of Takhisis, while the metallic dragons--gold, 
silver, bronze, copper and brass--have sided with the forces of goodness
and light. To the people of Ansalon no sound is more terrifying than the
thunderous roar of dragon wings. The history of Krynn has been wracked 
with confrontations between the gods of good and evil,played out on the
great chessboard of Ansalon.

See also: ROLEPLAY
