DRUID 

Druids are the protectors of Nature, believing in the sanctity of the natural 
world.  Although they worship Gods of several faiths and alignments, they all 
have a similar goal for the most part in the defense of nature.  Druids receive 
a wide variety of spells from their patron God.  They may only use weapons and
armor of the natural materials, save for a few select items used in ceremonies. 
Druids must possess above average wisdom and social skills.

See also: PRACTICE, SPELLS, CAST, MEM
