HOUSES HOUSE

Rules and Procedures for Townhouses on Age of Legends

1.  Townhomes are available on a first come first serve basis.  A player
can only have one townhouse regardless of the number of characters they
may have.

To purchase a townhome you must mail a formal request to the
aolapprovals@yahoo.com account. The mail should include your character
name and acknowledgement  that you have read and understand the AoL
housing rules and policies (contained in this document), since violation
of these rules could result in losing the house.  This mail should also
name any char who will be allowed to gain access and rent in that
house.  Only one additional 'guest' may be defined.

2.  Each townhouse consists of one room with a housekeeper that will
store your belongings.

3.  The cost to purchase a townhouse is 20p.  Taxes are due and payable
in monthly installments on the first day of every month (using the RL
calendar).  A new owner will need to pay taxes on the first of the month
after they purchase.  Monthly fees are 7p per occupant (a maximum of two
occupants are permitted) regardless of which city the townhouse is in.
It is the primary owners responsibility to make sure that their taxes
are paid in time.  They must make every effort to get the fees to the
designated imm in charge of housing.

4. The townhomes were designed to enhance our world and rp environment,
not to replace our rent system.  As mentioned above, the mobs in the
townhomes will be innkeepers.  Players are required to still rent, and
their housekeeper will store their things.

A change of clothing can be kept in the house.  Items left should be
strictly of the clothing variety or other accessories, like a lute.  If
a player is unsure they should ask or just rent the item until they can
check with an imm.

